4.00	Brandon_Shaffer	Brandon Shaffer	Brandon Shaffer (born March 22, 1971) is the current President of the Colorado State Senate representing Senate District 17, which encompasses the cities of Longmont, Lafeyette, Erie, and Louisville. Shaffer, a lifelong Democrat, was first elected as a State Senator in November 2004, and was reelected in 2008. Following the resignation of Senate President Peter Groff in 2009, Shaffer was elected to the post, while Senator John Morse (D-Colorado Springs) became Majority Leader. He is seeking the Democratic nomination for Colorado's 4th Congressional District.	
